|related=
}}
'''澳大利亚原住民'''（{{lang-en|Indigenous Australians}}）是{{le|澳大利亚土著|Aboriginal Australians}}（Aboriginal Australians）和[[托雷斯海峡岛民|托雷斯海峡岛民]]（Torres Strait Islanders）的總稱，是歐洲人殖民[[大洋洲|大洋洲]]之前居住在[[澳洲大陸|澳洲大陸]]及其附近島嶼的[[原住民|原住民]]族群的後代。

根據傳統用法，“澳洲土著”（Aborigines）指的是澳洲大陸、塔斯馬尼亞島以及一些其他臨近島嶼的原住民；而[[托雷斯海峽|托雷斯海峽]]位于澳洲東北的[[约克角半岛|约克角半岛]]與[[新幾內亞|新幾內亞]]之間，托雷斯海峽島民是該海峽中群島的[[美拉尼西亚|美拉尼西亚]]原住民。

“澳洲原住民”是籠統的稱呼，其包括的民族之間有很大區別，例如提維人（Tiwi people）、努恩嘎人（Noongar people）和托雷斯海峡岛民（Torres Strait Islanders）等都是不同的民族，屬於原住民的民族之間並不一定有密切的關聯或相同的起源。不同原住民社群和社會之間有很大的差異，每個社群都有自己獨特的文化、習俗和語言。當代的原住民更細分爲不同的當地社區。
<ref>{{cite journal|author=Hodge, Robert|url=http://wwwmcc.murdoch.edu.au/ReadingRoom/3.2/Hodge.html|title=Aboriginal truth and white media: Eric Michaels meets the spirit of Aboriginalism|journal=The Australian Journal of Media & Culture|volume=3|issue=3|year=1990|access-date=2015-09-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120721132745/http://wwwmcc.murdoch.edu.au/ReadingRoom/3.2/Hodge.html|archive-date=2012-07-21|dead-url=yes}}</ref>据估計，歐洲人移民開始時，原住民共有約250種語言，但現在大約只有120到145種語言仍然存在，其中絕大多數屬於瀕危語種，僅有13種不屬于瀕危語種。<ref name=ABS/><ref name="aiatsis.gov.au">[http://aiatsis.gov.au/publications/products/community-identity-wellbeing-report-second-national-indigenous-languages "Community, identity, wellbeing: The report of the Second National Indigenous Languages Survey" ''AIATSIS''] {{Wayback|url=http://aiatsis.gov.au/publications/products/community-identity-wellbeing-report-second-national-indigenous-languages |date=20150424032821 }}, 2014. Retrieved 18 May 2015.</ref>現代的土著大多數使用夾雜土著語詞彙並受土著語發音和語法構造影響的英語，這類英語語種稱爲“澳洲土著英語”。歐洲人移民開始時原住民人口按照不同的估計可能約為318,000人<ref name="pop_abs2">[http://www.abs.gov.au/ausstats/abs@.nsf/94713ad445ff1425ca25682000192af2/bfc28642d31c215cca256b350010b3f4!OpenDocument 1301.0 – Year Book Australia, 2002] {{Wayback|url=http://www.abs.gov.au/ausstats/abs@.nsf/94713ad445ff1425ca25682000192af2/bfc28642d31c215cca256b350010b3f4!OpenDocument |date=20110410054601 }} Australian Bureau of Statistics 25 January 2002</ref>或1,000,000人<ref name="pop_abs">Gough, Myles (11 May 2011) [https://web.archive.org/web/20120912060604/http://www.cosmosmagazine.com/news/4305/prehistoric-aboriginal-populations-australia-were-growing Prehistoric Australian Aboriginal populations were growing]. ''[[Cosmos_Magazine|Cosmos Magazine]]''.</ref>，人口分佈類似現在的澳洲人口分佈規律，大多數生活在東南部，以[[墨累河|墨累河]]為軸綫的地區.<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.3828/bfarm.2006.1.4| title = Becoming Australian| journal = Before Farming| volume = 2006| pages = 1| year = 2006| last1 = Pardoe | first1 = C. }}</ref>按照英文維基百科，澳洲現有原住民798,365人，

澳洲大陸最早的居民和現代澳洲原住民之間的關係在學術上尚無定論。在澳洲發現的最早的人類遺存是40,000年前的“蒙哥人”（Mungo Man），但根據[[线粒体DNA|线粒体DNA]]比較，蒙哥人與現在以及古代的澳洲原住民都沒有親屬關係。<ref>{{cite journal|author=Adcock, Gregory|url=http://www.pnas.org/content/98/2/537.full?sid=8f289c70-86e5-43cf-9d98-2c7b22612d47|title=Mitochondrial DNA sequences in ancient Australians: Implications for modern human origins|display-authors=etal|access-date=2015-09-21|archive-date=2015-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150130060114/http://www.pnas.org/content/98/2/537.full?sid=8f289c70-86e5-43cf-9d98-2c7b22612d47|dead-url=no}}</ref>而人類到達澳洲的時間本身在學術上也沒有定論，其中最早的估計認爲可能是125,000年前。<ref name="uow2004">[http://media.uow.edu.au/news/2004/0917a/index.html "When did Australia's earliest inhabitants arrive?"] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/684CJZgPP?url=http://media.uow.edu.au/news/2004/0917a/index.html |date=20120531081354 |dateformat=iso }}, University of Wollongong, 2004. Retrieved 6 June 2008.</ref> 

按照近年的研究，具較大可能性的是澳洲原住民是約70,000年前第一波離開非洲前往亞洲的古人的後裔，<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1126/science.1211177| title = An Aboriginal Australian Genome Reveals Separate Human Dispersals into Asia| journal = Science| volume = 334| issue = 6052| pages = 94| year = 2011| last1 = Rasmussen | first1 = M.| last2 = Guo | first2 = X.| last3 = Wang | first3 = Y.| last4 = Lohmueller | first4 = K. E.| last5 = Rasmussen | first5 = S.| last6 = Albrechtsen | first6 = A.| last7 = Skotte | first7 = L.| last8 = Lindgreen | first8 = S.| last9 = Metspalu | first9 = M.| last10 = Jombart | first10 = T.| last11 = Kivisild | first11 = T.| last12 = Zhai | first12 = W.| last13 = Eriksson | first13 = A.| last14 = Manica | first14 = A.| last15 = Orlando | first15 = L.| last16 = de la Vega | first16 = F. M.| last17 = Tridico | first17 = S.| last18 = Metspalu | first18 = E.| last19 = Nielsen | first19 = K.| last20 = Avila-Arcos | first20 = M. C.| last21 = Moreno-Mayar | first21 = J. V.| last22 = Muller | first22 = C.| last23 = Dortch | first23 = J.| last24 = Gilbert | first24 = M. T. P.| last25 = Lund | first25 = O.| last26 = Wesolowska | first26 = A.| last27 = Karmin | first27 = M.| last28 = Weinert | first28 = L. A.| last29 = Wang | first29 = B.| last30 = Li | first30 = J.| display-authors = 29}}</ref>在約60,000年前抵達澳洲。<ref name="BBSRC">[http://www3.imperial.ac.uk/newsandeventspggrp/imperialcollege/newssummary/news_23-9-2011-10-41-8 "Aboriginal Australians descend from the first humans to leave Africa, DNA sequence reveals"] {{Wayback|url=http://www3.imperial.ac.uk/newsandeventspggrp/imperialcollege/newssummary/news_23-9-2011-10-41-8 |date=20141006103055 }}, ''Biotechnology and Biological Sciences Research Council (BBSRC)''.</ref><ref name="illumina.com">[http://www.illumina.com/documents/icommunity/article_2012_04_Aboriginal_Genome.pdf Sequencing Uncovers a 9,000 Mile Walkabout] {{Wayback|url=http://www.illumina.com/documents/icommunity/article_2012_04_Aboriginal_Genome.pdf |date=20181121085215 }}. ''ICommunity Newsletter''. April 2012</ref>

1995年起，紅、黑兩色加上黃色太陽圖案的“[[澳洲土著旗|澳洲土著旗]]”和藍、綠兩色加上頭飾圖案的“[[托雷斯海峡岛民旗|托雷斯海峡岛民旗]]”在澳洲享有國家正式旗幟的地位。

== 族群與名稱 ==
[[File:Aboriginal_Australians_Distribution.jpg|thumb]]
===用詞===
[[File:Bathurst_Island_men.jpg|thumb]]
籠統來説，澳洲原住民種族都與所謂的[[澳洲人種|澳洲人種]]的一個分支有關係，<ref>{{cite journal|author=Huxley, Thomas|url=http://aleph0.clarku.edu/huxley/SM3/GeoDis.html|year=1870|title=On the Geographical Distribution of the Chief Modifications of Mankind|journal=Journal of the Ethnological Society of London|access-date=2015-09-22|archive-date=2010-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101212220953/http://aleph0.clarku.edu/huxley/SM3/GeoDis.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>但在社會、文化及語言方面各個土著及托雷斯海峽島民族群之間都有顯著的不同。

英語單詞“土著”（aboriginal）最遲在16世紀就已出現，意思是“第一或最早所知的、原生的”，詞源是拉丁語的''aborigines''，意即“來自”（''ab''）“源頭、開始”（''origo''）。<ref>[http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/aborigine Aborigine – Definition and More from the Free Merriam-Webster Dictionary] {{Wayback|url=http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/aborigine |date=20210414072328 }}. Merriam-webster.com (31 August 2012). Retrieved 2 August 2013.</ref>在澳洲，自從1789年（歐洲人殖民澳洲的第二年）開始就有使用“土著”（aboriginal）來形容澳洲的原住居民。不久後，大寫的“Aboriginal”（“土著”）就開始成爲所有原住民的通稱。

在英語中的習慣用法裏，“Aborigine”（單數名詞）和“Aboriginal”（形容詞）都被當作名詞“土著”使用。但由於歷史原因，在某些社群，使用這兩個詞來形容某一（或多個）個人的用法被視爲具有負面涵義，因此通常這樣的用法被認爲是粗魯、甚至冒犯的。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www0.health.nsw.gov.au/pubs/2004/pdf/aboriginal_terms.pdf |title=Communicating Positively: A guide to appropriate Aboriginal terminology |publisher=NSW Health |accessdate=3 August 2013 |archive-date=2013-09-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130922033118/http://www0.health.nsw.gov.au/pubs/2004/pdf/aboriginal_terms.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.slwa.wa.gov.au/dead_reckoning/private_archives/a-f/aboriginal_people|title = Dead Reckoning: a guide to family history research in WA: Aboriginal People|publisher = State Library of Western Australia|accessdate = 3 August 2013|archive-date = 2013-09-04|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130904125147/http://www.slwa.wa.gov.au/dead_reckoning/private_archives/a-f/aboriginal_people|dead-url = no}}</ref>較可接受的或較正確的用法是“土著澳洲人”（Aboriginal Australians
）或“土著”（Aboriginal people）（指個人時是“Aboriginal person”，“Aboriginal man”，“Aboriginal woman”等）。此外，囊括土著和托雷斯海峽島民的“澳洲原住民”（Indigenous Australians）在近年（特別是80年代以來）也使用得越來越多。<ref name=terminology-flinders>{{cite web|title=Appropriate Terminology, Indigenous Australian Peoples|url=http://www.ipswich.qld.gov.au/documents/community/appropriate_indigenous_terminoloy.pdf|work=General Information Folio 5|publisher=Flinders University, Adelaide, Australia|accessdate=10 May 2011|format=PDF|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110406134803/http://www.ipswich.qld.gov.au/documents/community/appropriate_indigenous_terminoloy.pdf|archivedate=2011年4月6日}}</ref>

===地區族群的自稱名稱===
“澳洲原住民”的廣義概念包括許多地區族群，這些族群經常使用來自當地原住民語言的自稱。這些包括：
[[File:Men_and_boys_playing_a_game_of_gorri_-_NMA-11726.jpg|thumb]]
* “庫利”（Koori、Koorie）：是[[新南威爾士|新南威爾士]]和[[維多利亞|維多利亞]]土著通用的自稱；
* “努納瓦”（Ngunnawal）：是分佈在[[澳洲首都領地|澳洲首都領地]]及周邊新南威爾士所屬地區的土著族群自稱；
* “古利”（Goorie）：是分佈在昆士蘭東南部及新南威爾士北部部分地區的土著族群自稱；
* “穆爾迪”（Murrdi）：是分佈在昆士蘭西南部及中部的土著族群自稱；
* “穆利”（Murri）：是昆士蘭其他部分（不使用古利和穆爾迪等特定名稱的地方）土著通用的自稱；
* “努恩嘎”（Nyungar、Noongar）:西澳州南部；
* “亞馬吉”（Yamatji）：西澳州中部；
* “丸蓋”（Wangai）：西澳州金礦區；
* “農嘎”（Nunga）：南澳州南部；
* “阿南古”（Anangu）：南澳州北部以及接壤的西澳州和北領地部分地區；
* “亞帕”（Yapa）：北領地中西部；
* “雍古”（Yolngu）：北領地[[阿纳姆地|阿纳姆地]]東部；
* “賓尼奇”（Bininj）：北領地[[阿纳姆地|阿纳姆地]]西部；
* “[[提維人|提維]]”（Tiwi）：北領地[[阿纳姆地|阿纳姆地]]附近海上的提維群島；
* “阿寧迪亞科瓦＂（Anindilyakwa）：北領地[[阿纳姆地|阿纳姆地]]附近海上的[[格鲁特岛|格鲁特岛]]；
* “巴拉瓦”（Palawah、Pallawah）：塔斯馬尼亞。

這些大族群中再有更細的分別，例如一位來自中部沙漠的“阿南古”人可能來自“皮姜加加拉”（Pitjantjatjara）、“陽昆加加拉”（Yankunytjatjara）、“納安亞加拉”（Ngaanyatjarra）、“魯理加”（Luritja）或“安諦基林亞”（Antikirinya）族群。据估計，在英國殖民者到來之前，澳洲大陸上的原住民人口大概在318,000到750,000之間。<ref name="pop_abs" />

===托雷斯海峽島民===
{{main|托雷斯海峡岛民}}
[[File:TorresStraitIslandsMap.png|thumb]]地圖]]

托雷斯海峽島民的遺傳和文化史都和土著的傳統不同。托雷斯海峽群島東部的島民尤其接近[[新幾内亞|新幾内亞]]的巴布亞人，使用的語言是[[巴布亞諸語言|巴布亞語]]的一種。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=ulk |title=Ethnologue report for language code: ulk |publisher=Ethnologue.com |accessdate=9 August 2009 |archive-date=2012-09-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120923030852/http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=ulk |dead-url=no }}</ref>因此，“澳洲土著”（Aboriginal Australians）不包括[[托雷斯海峽島民|托雷斯海峽島民]]。這也是近年來含義更廣的“澳洲原住民”或“澳洲原住民族”概念使用越來越多的原因之一。澳洲原住民中，有6%自認為純托雷斯海峽島民，另有4%自認為兼有托雷斯海峽島民和澳洲土著遺傳。<ref name="ATSI population">''[http://www.abs.gov.au/Ausstats/abs@.nsf/Previousproducts/1301.0Feature%20Article52004?opendocument&tabname=Summary&prodno=1301.0&issue=2004&num=&view= Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander population] {{Wayback|url=http://www.abs.gov.au/Ausstats/abs@.nsf/Previousproducts/1301.0Feature%20Article52004?opendocument&tabname=Summary&prodno=1301.0&issue=2004&num=&view= |date=20090515231152 }}'', Australian Bureau of Statistics 2004. Retrieved 2007-06-21.</ref>

托雷斯海峽群島包括過百個島嶼，<ref name="TSI">''[http://www.abc.net.au/ra/pacific/places/country/torres_strait_islands.htm Places – Torres Strait Islands] {{Wayback|url=http://www.abc.net.au/ra/pacific/places/country/torres_strait_islands.htm |date=20210319065129 }}'' [[ABC_Radio_(Australia)|ABC Radio Australia website]], 2005. Retrieved 21 June 2007.</ref>在1879年被昆士蘭兼併。<ref name="TSI"/>許多原住民組織的名稱中包含“土著及托雷斯海峽島民”的用法，以顯示[[托雷斯海峽島民|托雷斯海峽島民]]在澳洲原住民人群中的獨特身份和重要性。

澳洲原住民地權史中著名的1992年“马伯訴昆士蘭”案（Mabo v Queensland）的主角艾迪·马伯（Eddie Mabo）就來自[[托雷斯海峽|托雷斯海峽]]中的“摩爾”或稱墨累島。<ref name="TSI"/>

=== 塔斯馬尼亞 ===
{{main|塔斯馬尼亞原住民}}

==歷史==
===到達澳洲並定居===
[[File:Indig2.jpg|thumb]]船長及其船員與格威嘎爾部落土著在[[新南威爾士|新南威爾士]]的柯奈爾海岸的“第一次接觸”]]
大多數學者認爲人類于距今40,000至50,000年前到達澳洲，至遠可能達125,000年前。<ref name="uow2004" />根據基因分析得出的估計則是約44,000年前。<ref name="Rasmussen"/><ref name="Callaway."/>

在澳洲發現的最早的解剖學意義上的現代人類遺存（也是非洲以外最早的）是“芒哥人”，估計生活在距今42,000年前。<ref name = "pmid1259451">{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1038/nature01383| pmid = 12594511| title = New ages for human occupation and climatic change at Lake Mungo, Australia| journal = Nature| volume = 421| issue = 6925| pages = 837–40| year = 2003| last1 = Bowler | first1 = J. M. | last2 = Johnston | first2 = H. | last3 = Olley | first3 = J. M. | last4 = Prescott | first4 = J. R. | last5 = Roberts | first5 = R. G. | last6 = Shawcross | first6 = W. | last7 = Spooner | first7 = N. A. | bibcode = 2003Natur.421..837B}}</ref><ref name = "doisj.quascirev.2005.07.022">{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/j.quascirev.2005.07.022| title = Single-grain optical dating of grave-infill associated with human burials at Lake Mungo, Australia| journal = Quaternary Science Reviews| volume = 25| issue = 19–20| pages = 2469–2474| year = 2006| last1 = Olley | first1 = J. M. | last2 = Roberts | first2 = R. G. | last3 = Yoshida | first3 = H. | last4 = Bowler | first4 = J. M. | bibcode = 2006QSRv...25.2469O}}</ref>最初對稱爲“芒哥湖3號”遺骨與古代及現代土著進行的[[线粒体DNA|线粒体DNA]]比較分析顯示芒哥人與澳洲土著之間並沒有遺傳關係，<ref name="Adcock">{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1073/pnas.98.2.537| title = Mitochondrial DNA sequences in ancient Australians: Implications for modern human origins| journal = Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences| volume = 98| issue = 2| pages = 537–42| year = 2001| last1 = Adcock | first1 = G. J.| last2 = Dennis | first2 = E. S.| last3 = Easteal | first3 = S.| last4 = Huttley | first4 = G. A.| last5 = Jermiin | first5 = L. S.| last6 = Peacock | first6 = W. J.| last7 = Thorne | first7 = A.| bibcode = 2001PNAS...98..537A | pmid=11209053 | pmc=14622}}</ref>但這一結論在科學界也受到廣泛的不接受。有批評指出此一排序沒有經過獨立驗證，並且結果可能受到死後改變或DNA熱力破壞的影響。<ref name="pmid11388352">{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1126/science.292.5522.1655| title = Human Origins and Ancient Human DNA| journal = Science| volume = 292| issue = 5522| pages = 1655–6| year = 2001| last1 = Cooper | first1 = A.| pmid=11388352}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/S0047-2484(03)00106-4| title = The thermal history of human fossils and the likelihood of successful DNA amplification| journal = Journal of Human Evolution| volume = 45| issue = 3| pages = 203–17| year = 2003| last1 = Smith | first1 = C. I. | last2 = Chamberlain | first2 = A. T. | last3 = Riley | first3 = M. S. | last4 = Stringer | first4 = C. | last5 = Collins | first5 = M. J. | pmid=14580590}}</ref><ref>[http://australianmuseum.net.au/The-spread-of-people-to-Australia "The spread of people to Australia – Australian Museum"] {{Wayback|url=http://australianmuseum.net.au/The-spread-of-people-to-Australia |date=20110413002541 }}. ''australianmuseum.net.au''.</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|doi=10.1002/j.1834-4453.2001.tb00490.x |url=http://arts.anu.edu.au/grovco/Mungo3%20forum.pdf |title=Mitochondrial DNA sequences in ancient Australians: Implications for modern human origins |journal=Archaeology in Oceania |volume=36 |issue=3 |pages=163 |year=2001 |last1=Adcock |first1=G. J. |last2=Dennis |first2=E. S. |last3=Esteal |first3=S. |last4=Huttley |first4=G. A. |last5=Jermiin |first5=L. S. |last6=Peacock |first6=W. J. |last7=Thorne |first7=A. |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130515000756/http://arts.anu.edu.au/grovco/Mungo3%20forum.pdf |archivedate=2013-05-15 }}</ref>雖然這一受到爭議的分析結果似乎表示芒哥人是在當代人類的最早共同祖先出現之前就已分離出去的滅絕支系物種，<ref name="Adcock"/>至少芒哥國家公園管理機構認爲現在當地的土著是芒哥人的後代。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.visitmungo.com.au/mungo-lady-mungo-man |title=存档副本 |access-date=2016-02-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170125083151/http://www.visitmungo.com.au/mungo-lady-mungo-man |archive-date=2017-01-25 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>由於看管芒哥遺存的原著民据估計不會允許更多的創傷性研究，因此以後再進行獨立基因試驗的可能性不大。<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20140126190110/http://www-personal.une.edu.au/~pbrown3/LM3.html Lake Mungo 3]. [[University_of_New_England_(Australia)|University of New England]]</ref>

通常認爲，澳洲土著是一次单一遷徙中到達澳洲大陆的群體的後代，此群體是64,000年到75,000年前第一批离开非洲的現代人類的分支，<ref>[http://www.australiangeographic.com.au/journal/Aboriginal-Australians-the-oldest-culture-on-Earth.htm/ Aboriginal culture one of world's oldest] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111130031752/http://www.australiangeographic.com.au/journal/Aboriginal-Australians-the-oldest-culture-on-Earth.htm |date=2011-11-30 }}, Australian Geographic, 23 September 2011</ref>但也有少数意見認爲曾有数批遷徙。<ref>{{cite journal|author=Windschuttle, Keith |author2=Gillin, Tim |journal=Quadrant Magazine |date=June 2002 |title=The extinction of the Australian pygmies |url=http://www.sydneyline.com/Pygmies%20Extinction.htm |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130729090807/http://www.sydneyline.com/Pygmies%20Extinction.htm |archivedate=2013-07-29 }}</ref>最有可能的遷徙路綫是在海洋水位較低時用船進行“跳島”。有迹象表明，土著在很长一段时间内与现已滅絕的[[澳洲巨型動物群|澳洲巨型動物群]]生活在同一環境中。<ref>[http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2005/05/050531215140.htm Australia's Megafauna Coexisted With Humans] {{Wayback|url=http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2005/05/050531215140.htm |date=20210319065200 }}. ''ScienceDaily''. 31 May 2005.</ref>

就基因來説，澳洲原住民為[[美拉尼西亚|美拉尼西亚]]及[[巴布亞人|巴布亞人]]的近親，但有一部分的基因成份可能來自於和[[南亞|南亞]]人群的混血，或是近代歐洲人的影響。<ref name="illumina.com"/><ref name="AJHG">{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/j.ajhg.2010.07.008| title = Whole-Genome Genetic Diversity in a Sample of Australians with Deep Aboriginal Ancestry| journal = The American Journal of Human Genetics| volume = 87| issue = 2| pages = 297–305| year = 2010| last1 = McEvoy | first1 = B. P. | last2 = Lind | first2 = J. M. | last3 = Wang | first3 = E. T. | last4 = Moyzis | first4 = R. K. | last5 = Visscher | first5 = P. M. | last6 = Van Holst Pellekaan | first6 = S. M. | last7 = Wilton | first7 = A. N. }}<br />"Some individuals are close to the Oceanic cluster, composed of MEL and PAP individuals but most occupy a wide range on PC2 between Europeans and East Asians, generally falling in an area occupied by Central and South Asian populations."</ref>研究表明地理意義上的澳洲人群起源于單一的祖先族群，後代各地區組群之間分隔後，相對較少受到此後來自亞洲大陸的移民影響。其中[[新幾内亞|新幾内亞]]的巴佈亞人在約32,000年前從[[菲律賓|菲律賓]]的馬馬努亞人（Mamanwa）分離出來，並在約5,000年前人口迅速膨脹。<ref name="AJHG"/>据2011年的基因研究，澳洲土著、巴佈亞人和馬馬努亞人都帶有亞洲古人種[[丹尼索瓦人|丹尼索瓦人]]的部分基因，因此亞洲的現代人類和古人類在約44,000年前（澳洲大陸與巴佈亞新幾内亞分離、土著遷徙到澳洲之前）發生過雜交。<ref name="Rasmussen">{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1126/science.1211177| title = An Aboriginal Australian Genome Reveals Separate Human Dispersals into Asia| journal = Science| volume = 334| issue = 6052| pages = 94–98| year = 2011| last1 = Rasmussen | first1 = M.| last2 = Guo | first2 = X.| last3 = Wang | first3 = Y.| last4 = Lohmueller | first4 = K. E.| last5 = Rasmussen | first5 = S.| last6 = Albrechtsen | first6 = A.| last7 = Skotte | first7 = L.| last8 = Lindgreen | first8 = S.| last9 = Metspalu | first9 = M.| last10 = Jombart | first10 = T.| last11 = Kivisild | first11 = T.| last12 = Zhai | first12 = W.| last13 = Eriksson | first13 = A.| last14 = Manica | first14 = A.| last15 = Orlando | first15 = L.| last16 = de la Vega | first16 = F. M.| last17 = Tridico | first17 = S.| last18 = Metspalu | first18 = E.| last19 = Nielsen | first19 = K.| last20 = Avila-Arcos | first20 = M. C.| last21 = Moreno-Mayar | first21 = J. V.| last22 = Muller | first22 = C.| last23 = Dortch | first23 = J.| last24 = Gilbert | first24 = M. T. P.| last25 = Lund | first25 = O.| last26 = Wesolowska | first26 = A.| last27 = Karmin | first27 = M.| last28 = Weinert | first28 = L. A.| last29 = Wang | first29 = B.| last30 = Li | first30 = J.| display-authors = 29}}</ref><ref name="Callaway.">{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1038/news.2011.551| title = First Aboriginal genome sequenced| journal = Nature| year = 2011| last1 = Callaway | first1 = E. }}</ref>而2012年發表的一篇論文則報告有證據顯示4,000多年前曾有從[[印度|印度]]到北澳洲的較大規模的基因流動。這一時期也是澳洲考古記錄中工具技術及食物加工出現變化的時代，因此有推論兩者之間有關聯。<ref>{{Cite journal | author1 =  Irina Pugach | author2 = Frederick Delfin | author3 =Ellen Gunnarsdóttir | author4 =  Manfred Kayser | author5 = Mark Stoneking | year =  | title = Genome-wide data substantiate Holocene gene flow from India to Australia  | date= January 14, 2013 | journal = PNAS | volume = 110 | issue = 5 | pages = 1803–1808 | publisher =  | jstor =  | doi = 10.1073/pnas.1211927110 | url =  | format =  | accessdate = | pmid=23319617 | pmc=3562786}}</ref>
土著大多以[[狩獵採集|狩獵採集]]方式生存。雖然土著社會具有移動性或半[[遊牧民族|漁獵]]狀態，按照不同季節的食物資源變化淺析，但不同地區的生活方式和物質文化有很大的不同，而且在一些地區有永久性定居點<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.environment.gov.au/heritage/places/national/budj-bim/|title = National Heritage Places – Budj Bim National Heritage Landscape|publisher = Australian Government Department of Sustainability, Environment, Water, Population and Communities|accessdate = 13 August 2013|archive-date = 2021-04-18|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210418231755/http://www.environment.gov.au/heritage/places/national/budj-bim|dead-url = no}}</ref>及農業活動。<ref>Flood, Josephine (1984), "Archaeology of the Dreamtime" (Uni of Hawaii Press)</ref>澳洲大陸上人口密度最大的是東南部，特別是[[墨累河|墨累河]]谷。

有跡象表明，在歐洲人到達此地區前北澳洲的土著群落与[[望加錫|望加錫]]的[[海參|海參]]漁民有定期的貿易往來。<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1002/j.1834-4453.1986.tb00126.x| title = Macassans and the Aboriginal past| url = https://archive.org/details/sim_archaeology-in-oceania_1986-04_21_1/page/69| journal = Archaeology in Oceania| volume = 21| pages = 69–75| year = 1986| last1 = MacKnight | first1 = C. C. }}</ref>

据通行估計，歐洲人在1788年最初接觸土著時，土著人口大約为314,000。根據近年的考古發現也有論點認爲當時澳洲可以支持高達500,000至750,000的人口，一部分[[生態學|生態學家]]甚至認爲高達一百萬的人口也有可能。<ref name="pop_abs" /><ref name="NCCARF">[https://web.archive.org/web/20131113121606/http://www.nccarf.edu.au/wwwold/settlements-infrastructure/sites/www.nccarf.edu.au.settlements-infrastructure/files/file/ACCARNSI%20Node%202%20Discussion%20Paper%20-%20Population%20Distribution%20Migration%20and%20Climate%20Change%20in%20Australia%20%20Final.pdf ''Population Distribution, Migration and Climate Change in Australia: An Exploration'']. [[Adaptation_to_global_warming_in_Australia#National_Climate_Change_Adaptation_Research_Facility|NCCARF]] March 2012</ref><ref>Thomson, Neil (2001) "Indigenous Australia: Indigenous Health", p. 153 in James Jupp (ed), ''The Australian people: an encyclopedia of the nation, its people and their Origins'', Cambridge University Press. ISBN 0-521-80789-1 This article says the likely aboriginal population of Australia in 1788 was around 750,000 or even over a million. There was also a chart from the Australian Bureau of Statistics – Experimental Projections of the Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Population, Canberra, ABS, 1998 – with estimated populations for each state and for Australia as a whole total being 418,841.</ref>當時土著分爲250個“族”（nations），其中許多互相結盟，在一族内則有多個氏族（clans），少則5、6個，多則30、40個。每一族有其自己的語言，有些有數種語言。<ref>{{cite web|title=Gadian Society|url=http://www.gadian.org/Aboriginal.htm|work=Aboriginal|publisher=Gadian Society|accessdate=25 September 2013|archive-date=2021-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210319065220/http://www.gadian.org/Aboriginal.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>

就現在的州和領地來説，現在的[[昆士蘭州|昆士蘭州]]是與歐洲人接觸之前澳洲大陸上人口最密集的地區，約為新南威爾士的兩倍、維多利亞的六倍、塔斯馬尼亞的20倍。同時，原住民人口密度在新南威爾士東北部、[[卡奔塔利亞灣|卡奔塔利亞灣]]以西的北海岸（包括北領地及西澳的部分）都相對較高。<ref>[http://www.healthinfonet.ecu.edu.au/map-aboriginal-australia "Map of Aboriginal Australia"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.healthinfonet.ecu.edu.au/map-aboriginal-australia |date=20180324033018 }}. ''ecu.edu.au''.</ref>)

